(211, 1, '2006-01-28 16:45:09', '2006-01-28 21:45:09', '<a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0363771/"><img width="65" height="96" alt="Narnia" id="image241" class="alignleft" src="http://jevy.org/wp-content/uploads/2006/01/29m.thumbnail.jpg" /></a>Went this afternoon with <a href="http://flat-scan.livejournal.com/">Rob </a>to see Narnia this afternoon.  What a fantastic movie.  Not to mention that it''s based on a true story!!\n\nThis movie makes me wish I was at war.  Not that I''d enjoy seeing people die but for the reason of having a very tangeble view of what I am living for.  For example, during WWII, the world had a purpose to destroy and push back the Nazis.  Today what is the purpose being thrown at us?  Find a good job, get money, get a nice computer, play some video games, have a nice family, retire, sit on a beach somewhere then die.  Is this not how life is "supposed" to look for us?\n\nFrom the perspective of the bible, we are in fact at war.  God has a plan for me (and for everyone reading this too!) and desires for us to step into it.  Is it more worthwhile than retiring sipping margaritas on a sunny beach?  Well, Christ when he came said this:\n<blockquote><span id="en-NIV-26480" class="sup" />I am the gate; whoever enters through me will be saved. He will come in and go out, and find pasture. <span id="en-NIV-26481" class="sup" />The thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy; I have come that they may have life, and have it to the full.\n\n-- <a href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=john%2010:9-10;&version=31;">Matthew 10:9-10</a></blockquote>\nSo what does that practically look like for you?  Well, I don''t know.  I do know that God created you and so I''m sure he knows how that you can have life to the full.  Mind you, he''s not our suger daddy per se but he does want a relationship.  I hope you guys don''t find this cheesy over over spiritual.  I just think it makes sense.\n\nUpdate: Hopefully all cleared up <a href="http://jevy.org/2006/01/30/crazy-war-lover/">here</a>.', 'Based on a True Story', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'based-on-a-true-story', '', '', '2006-01-28 16:45:09', '2006-01-28 21:45:09', '', 0, 'http://jevy.org/?p=211', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(212, 1, '2006-01-30 14:39:26', '2006-01-30 19:39:26', 'I need to be clear from my <a href="http://jevy.org/2006/01/28/based-on-a-true-story/">last post</a> as I think I caused some <a href="http://jmaltais36.livejournal.com/357776.html">confusion</a>.  I think me trying to explain myself by using more words just gets me lost.  So I''ll try something different.\n<ul>\n	<li>War = Really bad</li>\n	<li>What I saw in Narnia was that the characters had a clear purpose for themselves, I would also like to have a clear purpose.</li>\n	<li>In this search, I am realizing that God has designed each of us to have a purpose from God.</li>\n</ul>\nI think that was all I was trying to say.  Hopefully that makes a bit more sense.', 'Crazy War Lover', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'crazy-war-lover', '', '', '2006-01-30 14:39:26', '2006-01-30 19:39:26', '', 0, 'http://jevy.org/?p=212', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(213, 1, '2006-02-01 14:18:49', '2006-02-01 19:18:49', 'Can I borrow (or buy) the Chronicles of Narnia set off someone?  The only reason I say buy is that it may be awhile since you get them back.  If you do lend them, I can assure you I remember who I borrowed them from.\n\nI need more reading material for the bus.  The newspaper is really not helping :P\n\n<strong>Update</strong>: AWESOME!  Thanks Rob.', 'Dream inspiration', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dream-inspiration', '', '', '2006-02-01 14:18:49', '2006-02-01 19:18:49', '', 0, 'http://jevy.org/?p=213', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(214, 1, '2006-02-02 17:50:04', '2006-02-02 22:50:04', 'Looks like I''ve been tagged by <a href="http://durak.livejournal.com/30672.html?view=39888">Alex</a>.<!--more-->\n\nFour jobs I’ve had\n<ol>\n	<li>Farm Boy Cashier</li>\n	<li>CTC Computer Training Toronto - Tech specialist and instructor</li>\n	<li>Elections Canada - Revision Agent Summer 2004</li>\n	<li>Carleton Univerity - Robot Design Engineer (I don''t really know if that''s actually what my job was)</li>\n</ol>\nFour movies I can watch over and over\n<ol>\n	<li>Lost in Translation</li>\n	<li>Spy Game</li>\n	<li>Outbreak</li>\n	<li>Shawshank Redemption</li>\n</ol>\nFour places I’ve lived\n<ol>\n	<li>Des Chouettes Lane - Orleans, ON</li>\n	<li>Bloor and Spadina - Toronto, ON</li>\n	<li>Ghent - Belgium (Only 5 weeks)</li>\n	<li>Russell Ave - Ottawa, ON</li>\n</ol>\nFour TV shows I love\n<ol>\n	<li>Lost (w00t w00t)</li>\n	<li>Law and Order: SVU (Lately it''s whacked out)</li>\n	<li>The National with Peter Mansbridge (I wish he was my grandpa or something)</li>\n	<li><a href="http://www.kennyvsspenny.tv/">Kenny vs. Spenny</a></li>\n</ol>\nFour places I’ve vacationed\n<ol>\n	<li>Backpacked - Belgium, France, Italy, Switzerland and the Netherlands</li>\n	<li>NYC</li>\n	<li>Vancouver</li>\n	<li>Halifax</li>\n</ol>\nFour of my favorite dishes\n<ol>\n	<li>Italian</li>\n	<li>Wings/Nachos with beer</li>\n	<li>Indian</li>\n	<li>Butter soaked popcorn and orange juice</li>\n</ol>\nFour sites I visit daily (only three really)\n<ol>\n	<li>Bloglines.com (all my friends'' and news blogs)</li>\n	<li>LJ friends</li>\n	<li><a href="http://www.whiteninjacomics.com/">White Ninja Comics</a></li>\n</ol>\nFour places I would rather be right now\n<ol>\n	<li>Switzerland</li>\n	<li>Clocktower on Tuesdays for cheap wings and beer night (is it dinner yet???)</li>\n	<li>Actually, that''s it really.. I''m quite happy right here</li>\n</ol>\nFour bloggers I am tagging (Do it or it''s bad for you health)\n<ul>\n	<li><a href="http://skofz.li