(218, 1, '2006-02-06 17:37:14', '2006-02-06 22:37:14', 'This is <a href="http://uk.tickle.com/test/inkblot/start.html">one sweet test</a>!  I''m trying not to put too much weight on it but it got some points bang on.\n<img width="96" height="96" alt="Curiosity" id="image249" class="alignright" src="http://jevy.org/wp-content/uploads/2006/02/curiosity.thumbnail.jpg" />You are full of questions about life, people, and your own potential. You spend more time than others imagining the possibilities for your life – and you''re open to things others are too afraid to consider. You have an almost physical need to know and do more. It''s only through new experiences that you feel a greater understanding of yourself and the world. You also have a rebellious streak that shows up when you feel unable to truly influence the world or circumstances around you. Your appetite for novel experiences also shows an openness others don''t have, but wish they did. Your psyche is very rich; the more you learn about it, the more you will understand who you really are.', '&#8220;Your unconscious mind is most driven by Curiosity&#8221;', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'your-unconscious-mind-is-most-driven-by-curiosity', '', '', '2006-02-06 17:37:14', '2006-02-06 22:37:14', '', 0, 'http://jevy.org/?p=218', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(219, 1, '2006-02-08 10:41:06', '2006-02-08 15:41:06', 'Hi there!  You may have gotten here from <a href="http://www.qrz.com">QRZ </a>(website with a catalog of many callsigns) or maybe I announced it with in a QSO (a conversation) I had with you. Maybe you''re simply interesting in learning about the world of Amateur Radio.   In any case, I hope you find this site interesting.\r\n\r\nI got licensed in Feburary of 2005 with my basic license and received the callsign VA3JEV shortly thereafter.  After buying a <a href="http://www.yaesu.com/indexVS.cfm?cmd=DisplayProducts&amp;ProdCatID=106&amp;encProdID=QYzjsxzj0SY%3D&amp;DivisionID=65&amp;isArchived=0">Yaesu FT-7800R</a>, I played around with APRS a bit as well as joined in on some local <a href="http://www.hamsexy.com/wiki/index.php/Net">nets </a>on the <a href="http://oarc.net/rptr/index.html">local repeaters</a>.  It was good getting some useful contacts and experience on the air.\r\n\r\nIn July 2005 however, the <a href="http://www.rac.ca">Radio Amateur of Canada</a> announced that morse code was no longer a requirement to get on <a href="http://www.hamsexy.com/wiki/index.php/HF">HF</a>.  This was pretty exciting as I was now able to get on the air and talk with people from around the world.  So now, here I am.\r\n\r\nI mostly work PSK31 on 20m at 14.070.150.  I would love to receive your QSL card.  My info is located at QRZ.com\r\n\r\nHere is my current station setup:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://radio.tentec.com/amateur/transceivers/516">Ten Tec Argo V</a> running <a href="http://www.hamsexy.com/wiki/index.php/QRP">QRP </a>most of the time</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.yaesu.com/indexVS.cfm?cmd=DisplayProducts&amp;ProdCatID=106&amp;encProdID=QYzjsxzj0SY%3D&amp;DivisionID=65&amp;isArchived=0">Yaesu FT-7800R</a> for 2m/70cm stuff.</li>\r\n	<li>Old school MFJ manual tuner</li>\r\n	<li>20m/40m "Shorty" antenna in an interted V at 30 feet.</li>\r\n	<li>2m/70cm J-pole.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Radio', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'radio', '', '', '2008-05-19 10:38:43', '2008-05-19 15:38:43', '', 0, 'http://jevy.org/?page_id=219', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(220, 1, '2006-02-08 11:05:18', '2006-02-08 16:05:18', 'That''s it then.  I got a call last night for a job position in the city and I have taken them up on it.  In a brief moment my hopes for spending another summer in Europe were dashed.  I am trusting that this is what I''m supposed to do this summer.  It''s going to be a pretty sweet job I''m sure.\nThat summer I had an absolute blast with the people who were here.  My heart wants to "re-create" that experience but I realize that will just be setting myself up for dissapointment.  Instead, I look forward to new summer filled with roadtrips, new adventures and lots of Ultimate.  Wh00p wh00p\n\nOh yeah.. and NYC for a couple of days of "Reading Week"', 'Plans Established', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'plans-established', '', '', '2006-02-08 11:05:18', '2006-02-08 16:05:18', '', 0, 'http://jevy.org/?p=220', 0, 'post', '', 0),
