(354, 1, '2006-11-09 23:21:29', '2006-11-10 03:21:29', '<div style="text-align: center"><img id="image404" alt="Lost" src="http://jevy.org/wp-content/uploads/2006/11/lost.jpg" /></div>\nYesterday the semi-season finale.  I cannot get over how crazy this show is.  It''s frustrating how they designed it to be addictive where you simply cannot guess anything right.  Why do I like it so much despite this?  Good stinking question.  If you don''t keep up with the show -- don''t start.  You need to watch _every episode_ to know what the crap is going on.\n\nVery very well done show though if you have days on end to catch up.  Mind you, it''s only back in February.', 'Lost', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lost-2', '', '', '2006-11-09 23:21:29', '2006-11-10 03:21:29', '', 0, 'http://jevy.org/?p=354', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(355, 1, '2006-11-15 00:40:57', '2006-11-15 04:40:57', 'I''ve taken plenty of blood tests that past couple of months.  My doc has been finding that in the past three of four tests in the past three months, my white blood cell count is unusually low.  I asked her what could be be the cause she nearly refuses to answer as it could be so many things.  I called my naturopath up and she''s looking into it but agrees it could be any number of things.  Could it be related to this Candida thing?  Goodness knows.  I do know that the good Lord loves me and is taking care of me.  Anyways, I got a referral for a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hematologist">Hematologist</a>.\nI''m crazy tired these days though.   I think I need to drink more water to flush my system... or something. :P', 'Hema-who?', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hema-who', '', '', '2006-11-15 00:40:57', '2006-11-15 04:40:57', '', 0, 'http://jevy.org/?p=355', 0, 'post', '', 0),
